> While we are talking bttv, do we have support for the Teppro cards? They
> are very popular here (Australia). I use it as
> 	options bttv  card=3 pll=2
> 	options tuner type=5
> but the "mute" work in reverse. Also, the volume control has no effect
> (should it if I do not run the sound through my soundcard, i.e. does the
> bttv have it's own volume control?).
There is a table in bttv.c, copy entry 3 to the end of the table for your
card, and then you can alter it to indicate how your board is wired. You
may want to join the video4linux list (see
	
http://roadrunner.swansea.linux.org.uk/v4l.shtml
)
bottom line: supporting your card directly with mute the right way around
is a table filling exercise
-
